Completed the review task: I found two substantive issues in `pulsar-core\pulsar-browser\src\main\kotlin\ai\platon\browser4\driver\chrome\dom\util\MicroDOMTreeNodeHelper.kt` — (1) `toNanoTreeInRangeRecursive()` pre-filters children before recursion, which can drop visible leaf nodes and in-range descendants under out-of-range wrappers from the nano tree / ARIA snapshot, and (2) `toInteractiveDOMTreeNodeList()` mixes `nodeId` with `paintOrder/backendNodeId` when computing `textBefore`, so adjacent text can be attached to the wrong interactive node.  
Recommended fixes: recurse first and prune only empty generated subtrees for the nano tree path, and compute `textBefore` from one consistent traversal order (ideally a single DFS visit index) instead of comparing mixed identifier domains.  
I appended this review and lessons learned to `coworker\tasks\300logs\2026\03\09\MEMORY.20260309.md`, and I verified the monthly memory already included the prior-day rollup so no monthly backfill was needed.


